Titolo: Excitebike 64

Anno: 2000

Descrizione: Excitebike 64 is a video game published by Nintendo and developed by Left Field Productions. It was released for the Nintendo 64 on April 30, 2000 in North America, June 23 in Japan, and June 8, 2001, in Europe. It is the second installment in the Excite series, acting as a sequel to Excitebike on the NES, and is the first 3D game in the series. Many real-life dirt bike gear brands are extensively featured throughout the game, such as Bell Helmets, Alpinestars and No Fear.
The game received positive reviews from critics and was later re-released for Wii U via the Virtual Console in 2016. A third game in the series, Excite Truck, was released in 2006 for the Wii.

Genere: Racing 

Valutazione: N/A
